HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 127
BY REPRESENTATIVE FREIBERG
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Teach For America for its efforts to improve educational
outcomes for students in Louisiana and throughout the United States
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Teach For America for its efforts to improve educational outcomes for
3 students in Louisiana and throughout the United States.
4 WHEREAS, Wendy Kopp founded Teach For America to address the national
5 teacher shortage and to improve academic outcomes for low-income children; the
6 organization launched in 1990 with three hundred eighty-four corps members in the five
7 founding regions of New York, Los Angeles, eastern North Carolina, rural Georgia, and
8 southern Louisiana; and
9 WHEREAS, Teach For America is a leadership development organization for those
10 who want to help students achieve the most critical educational milestones; today, the
11 organization celebrates it's thirty-fifth anniversary with a network of more than seventy
12 thousand leaders and more than one thousand eight hundred fifty leaders in Louisiana; these
13 individuals start in the classroom and remain in lifelong pursuit of the vision that all children
14 will be afforded the opportunity to receive a quality education; and
15 WHEREAS, Teach For America's mission is to find, develop, and support
16 exceptional leaders in order to expand access and opportunity for all children, and the
17 organization works to create an environment where educators, policymakers, parents, and
18 students work together to ensure that children have an adequate foundation; and
19 WHEREAS, Teach For America recruits outstanding leaders to serve as "corps
20 members"; these individuals commit to teach for two years in low-income communities,
21 where they can experience the challenges and rewards of creating and expanding
